title: For Sale:  "SUPER GONG"  Medium to Long range target system
postcontent:
Tired of making those long shots and being uncertain of your point of impact?  Well, here is an economical solution that works well and is extremely simple. 

Introducing the "variable report" steel gong target.  This target is a 20" cone plate with a reinforced 6" bulls eye center. The result is 2 distinct sound effects when hit. 

The 20" outer cone target is 7mm thick, extra hard spring/blade steel, (AR 300-400). This thinner convex style, hardened metal blade steel, rings much louder when hit than a piece of 1/2" AR500, and makes a very distinct "TINK" sound.  And the results to the target are the same, no damage. 

The 6" reinforced center bullseye is made from a piece of 1" thick hardened steel.  When hit, the bulls eye makes a very distinctive "THUD or KNOCK" sound.  The result is 2 different sounds, making it easier to distinguish a center hit versus an outside hit. 

This setup really shines out past 400-500 yds, and is very impressive at 1000 yds. At these ranges, 1/2 " AR500 is mostly an overkill for most anything smaller than 50 BMG. Not to mention it can be a lot harder to distinguish a center mass hit, or even hear a hit out at 800+ yds with smooth AR500. The cone design of this plate works much like a bell, plus the added benefit of deflecting copper and lead more rearward, instead of sideways or even back forward like you can get with a smooth plate.

But it doesn't stop there. This Super Gong comes with its own stand which is integrated all as one unit that folds up neatly for transport or storage. Setup and takedown takes literally 10 seconds or less and requires no tools or hardware.  The stand is basically a tripod design and is extremely stable and sturdy. Plus you can adjust the height from ground level to 5' without any tools or extra cut pieces. 

Key benefits of the stand:
-Made of wood 2x4x8's. These will absorb a lot of hits before they have to be replaced, plus they are much lighter than steel. Replacing them only requires a trip to the local lumberyard and a 1/2" drill bit. No specially cut flimsy pieces here!
-Tripod design is far more stable than a stand with cross members. Height adjustment is as simple as changing the pitch of the legs. Adjust target from ground level to 5' in order to compensate for terrain or brush.
-Target is mounted to stand using dense conveyor belting. This is far superior to chain or wire. Bullets only make tiny holes thru belting, you don't run the risk of breaking a chain with a bullet. Another added benefit from belting is the target will sway a lot less and returns to center quickly. None of the swinging effect you get from chain.

The approx. weight of steel target and stand is 45#.  If weight or handling is an issue, simply remove steel target from stand using two 3/4" wrenches.

Built to order

PRICE = $150 (gong and stand),  +$25 delivery to SW Idaho area

Custom options available, 
Contact me with any questions,
Thanks for looking
